<p>Good concept, but some errors stop me from upvoting this tale.</p>
<ul>
<li>SK-1 was used from 1961 to 1963, whereas Leonov, the first man to undertake extra-vehicular activity in 1965, used a Berkut suit. It's debatable, because the suit in question is not exactly an SK-1, but still.</li>
<li>Alexei calls his motherland Russia instead of USSR for some reason, and knows mythology all too well for a communist and a military person.</li>
<li>Life support in SK-1 is vehicle provided, and even a Berkut suit is only meant to last 45 minutes.</li>
</ul>

